Basic API

This excercise follows the instructuion provided by Python Coding for Public Policy @ NYU Wagner.



import requests

# Setting parameters
jimmy = {
    "api_key": "DEMO_KEY",
    "q" : "Jimmy McMillan",
    "sort": "-first_file_date",
}

# Load data in json format
response = requests.get("https://api.open.fec.gov/v1/candidates/" , params = jimmy)
data=response.json()
data

Nominatim API Geocoding Excercise

The search API allows you to look up a location from a textual description or address. Nominatim supports structured and free-form search queries.

The search query may also contain special phrases which are translated into specific OpenStreetMap (OSM) tags (e.g. Pub => amenity=pub). This can be used to narrow down the kind of objects to be returned.

import requests

ithaca = {
    "q": "City Center, Ithaca",
    "format" : "json"
}

response= requests.get("https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/search", 
params= ithaca,
headers={"user-agent": "Python in-class exercise"})

data_=response.json()
data_
[]

Reading into a DataFrame

import pandas as pd

candidates_with_funds = {
    "api_key": "DEMO_KEY",
    "has_raised_funds": "true",
}
response = requests.get("https://api.open.fec.gov/v1/candidates/", params=candidates_with_funds)
data = response.json()

candidates = data["results"]
pd.DataFrame(candidates)

Back to 311 data

From NYC Open Data Portal dataset page, click Export -> SODA API -> API Docs.

# Example: 311 requests from the last week

from datetime import datetime, timedelta

now = datetime.utcnow()
now
/var/folders/ls/4rhr7kfj5nd_v0fn499s11hm0000gn/T/ipykernel_15408/1794239729.py:5: DeprecationWarning:

datetime.datetime.utcnow() is deprecated and scheduled for removal in a future version. Use timezone-aware objects to represent datetimes in UTC: datetime.datetime.now(datetime.UTC).

datetime.datetime(2025, 4, 23, 5, 57, 56, 130947)
start = now - timedelta(weeks=1)
start
datetime.datetime(2025, 4, 16, 5, 57, 56, 130947)
start.isoformat()
'2025-04-16T05:57:56.130947'
# data id
data_id = "erm2-nwe9"

# params
in_past_week = {
    "$where": f"created_date > '{start.isoformat()}'",
}

url = f"https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/{data_id}.json"


response = requests.get(url, params=in_past_week)


data=response.json()
data
